1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,944
=Episode 12=
(Half A Sheet of Premium White Lambskin)

3
00:01:38,482 --> 00:01:41,322
When she acted as the good Samaritan
by sending you to the exam,

4
00:01:41,682 --> 00:01:42,842
did she think about me?

5
00:01:44,081 --> 00:01:45,322
Did she ever pity me?

6
00:01:46,441 --> 00:01:47,161
Was it my fault

7
00:01:48,042 --> 00:01:51,441
that she was poor
and married a man who beat her?

8
00:01:53,322 --> 00:01:54,441
Why blame me?

9
00:01:55,202 --> 00:01:56,641
That was just her fate.

10
00:01:58,361 --> 00:02:00,161
What gives you the right to question me?

11
00:02:06,842 --> 00:02:09,202
You'll never admit you're wrong.

12
00:02:09,882 --> 00:02:13,681
No matter how much you hurt others,
it's always their fault.

13
00:02:15,442 --> 00:02:20,121
Since childhood, you've torn and smashed
my belongings whenever you pleased.

14
00:02:21,361 --> 00:02:23,882
Because in your logic, I belong to you.

15
00:02:24,162 --> 00:02:25,762
Everything I have is yours.

16
00:02:28,641 --> 00:02:30,322
Whether it's your deceased daughter,

17
00:02:30,801 --> 00:02:32,202
your husband who left you,

18
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:34,322
or me,

19
00:02:36,241 --> 00:02:39,202
in your eyes,
we've never been whole people.

20
00:02:39,801 --> 00:02:41,361
We're just possessions to you.

21
00:02:43,202 --> 00:02:44,762
That includes everyone around me.

22
00:02:45,442 --> 00:02:47,042
We all have to dance to your tune.

23
00:02:54,561 --> 00:02:58,282
You'll pay for all the evil you've done.

24
00:03:01,762 --> 00:03:02,452
That, I promise.

25
00:03:11,762 --> 00:03:12,681
Don't forget

26
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:15,361
what I have in my hands.

27
00:03:33,282 --> 00:03:34,922
You have no right to threaten me.

28
00:03:37,282 --> 00:03:38,322
No right.

29
00:03:45,746 --> 00:03:49,560
(Shabei County)

30
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,672
(Tubao Village)

31
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:10,514
(Mr. Liu)

32
00:04:15,741 --> 00:04:17,761
Sir, I sent you my location.

33
00:04:17,761 --> 00:04:19,282
Come pick me up later.

34
00:04:20,681 --> 00:04:21,241
Thanks.

35
00:04:36,882 --> 00:04:39,480
(Liang Yi)

36
00:04:41,642 --> 00:04:42,922
My goodness, finally you're on.

37
00:04:42,922 --> 00:04:44,241
Where have you been?

38
00:04:44,241 --> 00:04:46,361
Everyone's looking for you.
Liu Xiaoran is frantic.

39
00:04:46,761 --> 00:04:47,922
He has time to look for me?

40
00:04:48,801 --> 00:04:50,522
Haven't the media been hounding him?

41
00:04:51,042 --> 00:04:54,121
The media have been grilling Liu Xiaoran
about the copyright.

42
00:04:54,121 --> 00:04:55,561
That's why he's looking for you.

43
00:04:55,561 --> 00:04:56,681
And one creator claims

44
00:04:57,241 --> 00:04:58,616
you're at the Thai-Myanmar border.

45
00:04:58,761 --> 00:05:00,201
Thai-Myanmar border?

46
00:05:00,561 --> 00:05:01,881
They even have photos as proof.

47
00:05:10,482 --> 00:05:12,482
Since when
is the Thai-Myanmar border this cold?

48
00:05:15,201 --> 00:05:18,121
My goodness, what are you doing
all the way out there?

49
00:05:20,722 --> 00:05:22,042
Are you looking for Wen Yuxiu?

50
00:05:22,441 --> 00:05:24,642
How did I just remember that now?

51
00:05:25,082 --> 00:05:27,361
This is more important
than the court hearing, really.

52
00:05:28,042 --> 00:05:28,842
I'm sorry.

53
00:05:29,761 --> 00:05:31,842
Okay, the copyright lawsuit

54
00:05:32,482 --> 00:05:33,642
is postponed until next week.

55
00:05:34,241 --> 00:05:36,522
You must come back
no matter what, understand?

56
00:05:38,082 --> 00:05:38,761
I promise.

57
00:05:39,922 --> 00:05:40,681
One more thing.

58
00:05:41,121 --> 00:05:43,922
Liu Xiaoran has also hired a lawyer
for the divorce.

59
00:05:44,441 --> 00:05:47,321
His lawyer contacted me today.

60
00:05:47,922 --> 00:05:48,922
They want to negotiate.

61
00:05:49,361 --> 00:05:50,561
They mainly have two demands.

62
00:05:50,842 --> 00:05:53,801
First, the divorce can't be made public.

63
00:05:54,001 --> 00:05:54,522
Second,

64
00:05:56,082 --> 00:05:57,042
the property division.

65
00:05:57,801 --> 00:05:59,001
He thinks you want too much.

66
00:06:00,001 --> 00:06:01,681
His attitude has been clear throughout.

67
00:06:01,922 --> 00:06:03,722
He couldn't care less
about getting divorced.

68
00:06:04,282 --> 00:06:07,042
What he cares about
is the real impact this has on him.

69
00:06:07,482 --> 00:06:10,922
Liu Xiaoran's attitude isn't surprising.

70
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:14,522
After all, anyone in his position
would find it hard to accept.

71
00:06:15,121 --> 00:06:16,441
Thinking about the past,

72
00:06:16,842 --> 00:06:17,642
it must hurt

73
00:06:18,441 --> 00:06:19,441
deep down, right?

74
00:06:20,201 --> 00:06:21,482
I have no expectations of him.

75
00:06:22,282 --> 00:06:23,361
Why would I feel hurt?

76
00:06:24,922 --> 00:06:25,922
Alright.

77
00:06:26,321 --> 00:06:27,801
Take care of yourself.

78
00:06:28,922 --> 00:06:30,522
Don't worry. I'm hanging up now.

79
00:06:30,801 --> 00:06:31,441
Bye-bye.

80
00:06:35,761 --> 00:06:36,522
Where are you?

81
00:06:37,201 --> 00:06:39,416
I called your home.
Your mom said you're not back.

82
00:06:39,761 --> 00:06:41,201
Not in Northern Myanmar. Relax.

83
00:06:41,801 --> 00:06:42,761
Northern Myanmar?

84
00:06:43,241 --> 00:06:45,042
All eyes are on you right now.

85
00:06:45,282 --> 00:06:47,082
What exactly is your game?

86
00:06:47,321 --> 00:06:48,121
Why are you nervous?

87
00:06:48,842 --> 00:06:50,201
Haven't you always been clever?

88
00:06:50,722 --> 00:06:53,522
You even colluded with the publisher
to twist the truth.

89
00:06:54,328 --> 00:06:55,008
What do you fear?

90
00:06:57,881 --> 00:07:00,121
Xiaoming, come back.

91
00:07:00,761 --> 00:07:01,922
Let's talk properly.

92
00:07:02,441 --> 00:07:04,561
It's time to settle this.

93
00:07:04,962 --> 00:07:05,722
Liu Xiaoran,

94
00:07:06,121 --> 00:07:08,962
had you stopped publishing a month ago,
none of this would've happened.

95
00:07:09,642 --> 00:07:12,888
Two weeks ago, by giving me
the copyright and pulling the book,

96
00:07:12,888 --> 00:07:13,784
you could've saved it.

97
00:07:14,162 --> 00:07:14,962
You chose neither.

98
00:07:15,282 --> 00:07:17,441
To protect the reputation
you gained through deceit,

99
00:07:17,441 --> 00:07:18,642
you drove me into a corner.

100
00:07:19,042 --> 00:07:19,642
What?

101
00:07:21,001 --> 00:07:22,042
I can't fight back?

102
00:07:22,642 --> 00:07:24,761
Yes, I have other plans.

103
00:07:25,121 --> 00:07:27,842
But we're opponents now,
so I won't tell you.

104
00:07:28,441 --> 00:07:29,001
Bye.

105
00:07:40,114 --> 00:07:41,816
(Liu Xiaoran)

106
00:07:48,914 --> 00:07:50,393
(Liu Xiaoran)

107
00:07:50,393 --> 00:07:53,624
(Rejected)

108
00:08:12,482 --> 00:08:13,642
Tubao Village. We're here.

109
00:08:13,842 --> 00:08:15,361
Travelers to Tubao Village, get off.

110
00:08:21,482 --> 00:08:22,441
Everyone, wake up.

111
00:08:22,441 --> 00:08:23,561
We're at Tubao Village.

112
00:08:23,561 --> 00:08:24,441
- Get off now.
- Wait.

113
00:08:24,441 --> 00:08:25,162
Right away.

114
00:08:25,642 --> 00:08:26,922
Hurry up. Time to get off.

115
00:08:29,962 --> 00:08:31,441
Anyone needing to get off, do it now.

116
00:10:37,882 --> 00:10:39,681
What kind of technological era is this?

117
00:10:40,402 --> 00:10:43,481
Lose a phone,
and we're back in the Stone Age.

118
00:10:44,362 --> 00:10:45,402
Darn technology.

119
00:10:46,362 --> 00:10:47,681
Darn technology.

120
00:12:18,362 --> 00:12:20,882
Ren Xiaoming? Xiaoming, get up.

121
00:12:21,681 --> 00:12:22,801
How come you're lying here?

122
00:12:24,882 --> 00:12:26,882
You can't lie here. Wake up.

123
00:12:30,002 --> 00:12:31,341
Xiaoming, get up.

124
00:12:34,642 --> 00:12:35,402
Get up quickly.

125
00:13:51,882 --> 00:13:52,762
Feeling better now?

126
00:13:58,961 --> 00:14:01,801
How come a young girl like you
wandered alone into this wilderness?

127
00:14:02,282 --> 00:14:04,522
Luckily, I was coming down
the mountain hauling corn.

128
00:14:05,081 --> 00:14:06,642
Otherwise, you wouldn't have met me.

129
00:14:16,681 --> 00:14:17,481
Do you hear that?

130
00:14:18,642 --> 00:14:19,841
Wolves are in the mountains.

131
00:14:20,321 --> 00:14:21,081
You're lucky.

132
00:14:22,441 --> 00:14:24,162
Due to the blizzard, the wolves stay in.

133
00:14:35,362 --> 00:14:37,362
Where are you headed?
I can give you a ride.

134
00:14:37,961 --> 00:14:39,402
I'm going to Tubao Village.

135
00:14:41,762 --> 00:14:43,201
Which family are you from?

136
00:14:43,201 --> 00:14:44,402
Why haven't I seen you before?

137
00:14:45,162 --> 00:14:47,681
Are you from Tubao Village?

138
00:14:49,242 --> 00:14:50,362
I'm looking for someone.

139
00:14:50,801 --> 00:14:51,841
Who are you looking for?

140
00:14:54,081 --> 00:14:55,042
The Hao family.

141
00:14:57,042 --> 00:14:58,321
Who in the Hao family?

142
00:14:59,122 --> 00:14:59,882
Hao Ying.

143
00:15:08,122 --> 00:15:09,201
I am Hao Ying.

144
00:15:12,122 --> 00:15:12,841
What do you want?

145
00:15:18,681 --> 00:15:19,801
You're Mr. Hao?

146
00:15:23,282 --> 00:15:24,242
What a coincidence.

147
00:15:26,681 --> 00:15:27,642
What do you want?

148
00:15:29,801 --> 00:15:32,961
I'm Ren Xiaoming,
a reporter for a travel magazine.

149
00:15:33,362 --> 00:15:36,601
I'd like to do a feature on your village
as an authentic rural community.

150
00:15:38,642 --> 00:15:39,841
How do you know about me?

151
00:15:41,681 --> 00:15:42,481
My uncle.

152
00:15:43,522 --> 00:15:47,162
He was the accountant
at your Qidaohezi Farm,

153
00:15:48,362 --> 00:15:48,862
Zhao.

154
00:15:50,321 --> 00:15:51,001
You know? Zhao.

155
00:15:54,882 --> 00:15:56,282
It's okay if you don't recall him.

156
00:15:57,282 --> 00:15:58,601
But he remembers you.

157
00:15:59,162 --> 00:16:00,402
He said you're really amazing.

158
00:16:01,201 --> 00:16:03,522
Back then, no matter
how sick the livestock was,

159
00:16:03,801 --> 00:16:06,402
as long as it reached you,
you could save it.

160
00:16:08,441 --> 00:16:09,481
Yes, right.

161
00:16:11,642 --> 00:16:14,162
He knew I was coming
to your village for this feature

162
00:16:14,481 --> 00:16:15,961
and thought since you live there,

163
00:16:16,441 --> 00:16:18,642
maybe you could help me out.

164
00:16:20,201 --> 00:16:23,282
Alright, someone from Qidaohezi
is like family.

165
00:16:24,441 --> 00:16:25,882
Now that you've found me,

166
00:16:26,201 --> 00:16:28,201
consider it like coming home.

167
00:16:29,362 --> 00:16:30,002
Thank you.

168
00:16:30,481 --> 00:16:31,081
Let's go.

169
00:16:31,801 --> 00:16:32,481
Hold on tight.

170
00:16:40,362 --> 00:16:41,162
Hao,

171
00:16:42,201 --> 00:16:43,681
where'd you find such a beauty?

172
00:16:43,882 --> 00:16:44,961
- A relative.
- So pretty.

173
00:16:44,961 --> 00:16:45,961
She's come to visit me.

174
00:16:46,162 --> 00:16:47,122
You're lucky.

175
00:16:47,441 --> 00:16:48,162
Look.

176
00:16:48,162 --> 00:16:49,321
Finding such a partner, huh?

177
00:16:49,441 --> 00:16:50,242
Look at this beauty.

178
00:16:50,362 --> 00:16:51,002
Impressive.

179
00:16:51,002 --> 00:16:51,801
This is my relative.

180
00:17:02,201 --> 00:17:02,762
We're here.

181
00:17:16,681 --> 00:17:17,281
Get off.

182
00:17:32,642 --> 00:17:33,201
My kid.

183
00:17:42,001 --> 00:17:42,761
How old are you?

184
00:17:43,521 --> 00:17:46,562
Ignore her,
that deaf and mute unlucky thing.

185
00:17:47,082 --> 00:17:47,842
She's 17.

186
00:17:55,082 --> 00:17:55,582
Don't fear.

187
00:17:55,922 --> 00:17:56,441
It's chained.

188
00:17:57,481 --> 00:17:59,162
Come inside. It's cold out.

189
00:18:04,241 --> 00:18:04,882
Come on in.

190
00:18:15,441 --> 00:18:16,681
Come inside, Ms. Ren.

191
00:18:17,922 --> 00:18:18,882
Have some hot water.

192
00:18:21,041 --> 00:18:22,882
Mr. Hao, where's your wife?

193
00:18:24,201 --> 00:18:24,701
What?

194
00:18:27,362 --> 00:18:30,001
You seem to be raising the kid alone.
Is your wife not here?

195
00:18:34,842 --> 00:18:35,481
She's dead.

196
00:18:37,001 --> 00:18:38,041
Been dead for years.

197
00:18:53,001 --> 00:18:53,721
Dead?

198
00:18:55,721 --> 00:18:57,681
Time of death was Day 1
of Chinese New Year, 2007.

199
00:18:58,082 --> 00:19:00,201
The death certificate
was issued by the town clinic.

200
00:19:00,562 --> 00:19:02,001
COD was postpartum hemorrhage.

201
00:19:06,482 --> 00:19:09,241
(Medical Certificate of Death:
Wen Yuxiu)

202
00:19:09,241 --> 00:19:09,802
Hello.

203
00:19:11,201 --> 00:19:11,761
I need a card.

204
00:19:11,922 --> 00:19:13,041
Please queue here.

205
00:19:16,041 --> 00:19:17,842
Fill out your personal information here.

206
00:19:21,322 --> 00:19:22,721
Yes, just fill this out.

207
00:19:38,898 --> 00:19:41,721
(The Voyage of the Beagle)

208
00:19:41,721 --> 00:19:44,082
(The Voyage of the Beagle.)

209
00:19:44,441 --> 00:19:46,001
This book will tell you

210
00:19:46,362 --> 00:19:48,842
how vast the world is
and how far one can travel.

211
00:19:49,721 --> 00:19:52,041
Go out and see the world.

212
00:20:14,994 --> 00:20:18,200
(Wen Yuxiu's Tomb)

213
00:21:11,001 --> 00:21:14,041
(Ms. Zhou has passed away.
We'll never see her again.)

214
00:21:16,946 --> 00:21:19,576
(Ren Xiaoming: Ms. Zhou has passed away.
We will never see her again)

215
00:22:04,761 --> 00:22:05,602
Mr. Hao.

216
00:22:07,562 --> 00:22:08,562
You bought the phone?

217
00:22:09,241 --> 00:22:12,001
All settled.
Thanks for lending me money.

218
00:22:12,802 --> 00:22:13,842
I'll pay you back later.

219
00:22:13,842 --> 00:22:14,562
No rush.

220
00:22:15,362 --> 00:22:17,322
Did you try street food
in town yesterday?

221
00:22:19,241 --> 00:22:21,001
Wasteful thing. You fail at everything.

222
00:22:30,721 --> 00:22:31,362
Wasteful thing.

223
00:22:32,402 --> 00:22:33,041
Mr. Hao.

224
00:22:34,281 --> 00:22:35,441
If you're free later,

225
00:22:35,441 --> 00:22:37,041
could I ask you some questions?

226
00:22:37,681 --> 00:22:38,201
What for?

227
00:22:38,481 --> 00:22:39,802
I want to interview you.

228
00:22:40,001 --> 00:22:40,721
Interview me?

229
00:22:42,162 --> 00:22:43,802
What's there to interview me about?

230
00:22:43,802 --> 00:22:45,122
You're very important.

231
00:22:45,122 --> 00:22:45,681
Really?

232
00:22:46,562 --> 00:22:47,062
Alright.

233
00:22:47,362 --> 00:22:48,082
Let's go inside.

234
00:22:48,201 --> 00:22:48,802
Do it inside.

235
00:22:51,481 --> 00:22:53,922
Is there any place to stay
in the village?

236
00:22:55,521 --> 00:22:58,201
Or you could make do at my place.

237
00:22:59,241 --> 00:23:00,122
Are you sure?

238
00:23:00,602 --> 00:23:02,642
No worries.
My daughter will keep you company.

239
00:23:02,802 --> 00:23:04,122
I'll go to the village committee.

240
00:23:04,184 --> 00:23:05,904
Stay here.
It's convenient for my interview.

241
00:23:06,402 --> 00:23:07,322
- Makes sense.
- Right?

242
00:23:07,422 --> 00:23:07,922
Thank you.

243
00:23:07,922 --> 00:23:09,162
Don't go out at night.

244
00:23:09,162 --> 00:23:10,922
I'll let the dog out at night. It bites.

245
00:23:12,922 --> 00:23:14,001
What are you staring at?

246
00:23:15,362 --> 00:23:15,922
Get to work.

247
00:23:16,362 --> 00:23:18,441
She's narrow-minded.
Never seen a city person before.

248
00:23:18,602 --> 00:23:19,521
Sorry for that.

249
00:23:36,842 --> 00:23:39,201
Ms. Ren, you should rest.

250
00:23:39,761 --> 00:23:40,721
Well, I'm off.

251
00:23:41,342 --> 00:23:41,842
Got it.

252
00:23:41,842 --> 00:23:43,312
I'll let the dog out. Stay inside.

253
00:23:43,480 --> 00:23:44,041
Okay.

254
00:23:44,882 --> 00:23:45,382
Come here.

255
00:23:46,201 --> 00:23:48,681
First, feed the livestock later.

256
00:23:49,082 --> 00:23:52,122
Then boil some water for Ms. Ren
to soak her feet. Got it?

257
00:23:55,322 --> 00:23:55,842
Come out.

258
00:24:38,162 --> 00:24:40,818
(Pechoin)

259
00:24:50,354 --> 00:24:53,234
(Chinese Language Knowledge Dictionary)

260
00:24:57,266 --> 00:24:58,552
(A Life Unfaced: Biography of Lu Xun)

261
00:25:00,370 --> 00:25:01,816
(Small Dictionary of Chinese Idioms)

262
00:25:47,842 --> 00:25:49,001
Wen's Shoe Shop.

263
00:26:45,281 --> 00:26:47,192
It's okay. I can do it myself.

264
00:26:57,240 --> 00:26:58,201
Can you hear me?

265
00:27:02,761 --> 00:27:03,402
A little?

266
00:27:07,802 --> 00:27:09,802
Don't be afraid. I won't hurt you.

267
00:27:10,362 --> 00:27:12,241
Sleep here tonight. With me.

268
00:27:13,001 --> 00:27:14,521
I won't tell him, okay?

269
00:27:15,201 --> 00:27:15,842
Don't be scared.

270
00:27:56,818 --> 00:27:59,288
(Take me away)

271
00:28:02,162 --> 00:28:03,802
Come inside. Let's talk inside.

272
00:28:04,201 --> 00:28:04,701
It's fine.

273
00:28:08,761 --> 00:28:10,681
Alright, I won't pull you in.

274
00:28:14,041 --> 00:28:15,162
I do want to take you away.

275
00:28:16,001 --> 00:28:17,642
But if I take you out now,

276
00:28:18,882 --> 00:28:19,961
if Hao Ying

277
00:28:21,041 --> 00:28:21,562
catches you

278
00:28:22,500 --> 00:28:23,260
and takes you back,

279
00:28:23,681 --> 00:28:24,481
it'll be too risky.

280
00:28:25,122 --> 00:28:27,441
He'll hit you harder
and yell at you more.

281
00:28:27,882 --> 00:28:29,162
And if he reports to the police,

282
00:28:29,842 --> 00:28:31,281
they'll still bring you back.

283
00:28:31,882 --> 00:28:32,681
Understand?

284
00:28:33,842 --> 00:28:34,922
Give me some time.

285
00:28:35,802 --> 00:28:37,001
I will definitely get you

286
00:28:37,001 --> 00:28:38,281
out of here safely.

287
00:28:39,402 --> 00:28:39,922
Trust me.

288
00:29:41,642 --> 00:29:43,602
(Do you know the way out?)

289
00:29:45,642 --> 00:29:46,721
(I've been looking for it,)

290
00:29:47,602 --> 00:29:48,882
(but can't find the way out.)

291
00:30:15,890 --> 00:30:18,201
(Excellent)

292
00:30:18,201 --> 00:30:21,001
(Bai Shu, this essay is well written.)

293
00:30:21,642 --> 00:30:23,322
May you grow wings for your dreams

294
00:30:23,802 --> 00:30:25,842
and become a tree traveling the world.

295
00:30:46,082 --> 00:30:47,122
What are you doing?

296
00:30:52,201 --> 00:30:53,362
Ms. Zhou died.

297
00:30:58,521 --> 00:30:59,521
How?

298
00:31:00,402 --> 00:31:02,362
Hemorrhage during childbirth.

299
00:31:10,241 --> 00:31:11,521
Don't be too upset.

300
00:31:14,322 --> 00:31:16,201
That place is remote

301
00:31:17,602 --> 00:31:19,001
with poor medical conditions.

302
00:31:20,922 --> 00:31:22,922
Such things happen.

303
00:31:27,281 --> 00:31:29,162
If you hadn't reported her,

304
00:31:29,842 --> 00:31:31,402
she wouldn't have left school.

305
00:31:32,721 --> 00:31:34,481
If you hadn't told her husband,

306
00:31:35,521 --> 00:31:37,481
she wouldn't have been taken back there

307
00:31:38,842 --> 00:31:40,041
and even died.

308
00:31:44,681 --> 00:31:45,521
If...

309
00:31:48,041 --> 00:31:50,281
If she hadn't barged in that day,

310
00:31:51,041 --> 00:31:53,402
we would've reconciled.

311
00:31:58,082 --> 00:31:59,041
You wouldn't

312
00:31:59,802 --> 00:32:01,082
have kept the memory

313
00:32:01,082 --> 00:32:03,281
of me stopping you
from the high school entrance exam.

314
00:32:04,602 --> 00:32:07,041
You wouldn't have run away
from me repeatedly.

315
00:32:08,802 --> 00:32:11,922
You wouldn't have seen me as your enemy.

316
00:32:17,842 --> 00:32:18,802
Death

317
00:32:21,041 --> 00:32:23,362
is truly a simple thing.

318
00:32:24,922 --> 00:32:27,681
Those who run away, those who are weak,

319
00:32:28,041 --> 00:32:29,802
in the end, all choose death.

320
00:32:32,481 --> 00:32:33,681
Living is pitiful.

321
00:32:35,322 --> 00:32:37,041
Living is hard.

322
00:32:40,402 --> 00:32:41,681
Then why don't you just die?

323
00:32:47,642 --> 00:32:49,281
Do you hate me that much?

324
00:32:53,362 --> 00:32:56,922
Because of her existence,
you see me as even more of an enemy.

325
00:33:04,530 --> 00:33:07,128
(Shabei County, Dong Township)

326
00:33:37,681 --> 00:33:39,362
Go back!

327
00:33:44,402 --> 00:33:45,802
Sir, stop!

328
00:33:46,041 --> 00:33:47,322
Can't stop. We're in a hurry.

329
00:33:48,201 --> 00:33:49,281
Sit down. It's dangerous.

330
00:33:53,041 --> 00:33:53,802
Still running?

331
00:33:54,602 --> 00:33:55,162
Get up!

332
00:33:59,082 --> 00:33:59,582
Move!

333
00:34:00,642 --> 00:34:01,142
Move!

334
00:34:13,842 --> 00:34:14,481
(I'm sorry.)

335
00:34:14,722 --> 00:34:16,601
(I can't take you with me right now.)

336
00:34:17,521 --> 00:34:18,441
(But I promise.)

337
00:34:19,322 --> 00:34:20,922
(I promise, I will find a way)

338
00:34:21,282 --> 00:34:23,121
(to rescue you fair and square.)

339
00:34:31,601 --> 00:34:32,121
Ma'am.

340
00:34:32,121 --> 00:34:32,682
Li Meng.

341
00:34:33,121 --> 00:34:33,641
Come on.

342
00:34:33,641 --> 00:34:34,141
Hurry.

343
00:34:34,641 --> 00:34:35,242
Sit down.

344
00:34:36,161 --> 00:34:38,041
What's so urgent
that you asked to meet me?

345
00:34:40,001 --> 00:34:42,882
I want to tell you that
after I went back, I remembered

346
00:34:43,561 --> 00:34:45,481
the last time
there was news of Wen Yuxiu

347
00:34:45,882 --> 00:34:47,121
wasn't 2004.

348
00:34:47,441 --> 00:34:48,802
It was 2007.

349
00:34:49,001 --> 00:34:51,161
2007? Are you sure?

350
00:34:51,441 --> 00:34:53,842
I'm sure. Xiaoming took
the gaokao exam that year.

351
00:34:54,161 --> 00:34:56,242
I forgot the time
of her high school entrance exam.

352
00:34:56,561 --> 00:34:58,402
But I remember her gaokao exam time.

353
00:34:59,202 --> 00:35:01,001
On Day 1
of the Chinese New Year in 2007,

354
00:35:01,882 --> 00:35:03,282
a strange phone number called.

355
00:35:04,722 --> 00:35:06,561
Then, what did she say on the phone?

356
00:35:07,882 --> 00:35:09,121
She didn't speak.

357
00:35:12,842 --> 00:35:15,641
She was just breathing very rapidly.

358
00:35:15,641 --> 00:35:17,682
Then how could you be sure
it was her calling?

359
00:35:19,441 --> 00:35:20,202
The breathing.

360
00:35:20,922 --> 00:35:23,362
I heard her breathing.
It was definitely her.

361
00:35:24,722 --> 00:35:25,842
(Wasn't she dead?)

362
00:35:26,624 --> 00:35:27,544
(How is that possible?)

363
00:35:29,722 --> 00:35:30,601
The breathing.

364
00:35:30,962 --> 00:35:32,462
(Last news from Wen Yuxiu, 2007,
Unknown number, No speech, Breathing)

365
00:35:33,601 --> 00:35:37,161
That new book written by Liu Xiaoran,
Ren Xiaoming's husband,

366
00:35:37,362 --> 00:35:38,882
is called 'Breathe.'

367
00:35:43,601 --> 00:35:44,481
Is there a connection?

368
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:50,441
Hi.

369
00:35:52,041 --> 00:35:54,081
Meiyan, you bought so many shoes?

370
00:35:54,802 --> 00:35:56,682
Every pair I tried,
they said looked great.

371
00:35:56,682 --> 00:35:58,041
- They do.
- They kept saying so.

372
00:35:58,041 --> 00:35:59,202
We bought four or five pairs.

373
00:35:59,202 --> 00:35:59,702
Yeah.

374
00:36:00,041 --> 00:36:00,842
Can you wear them?

375
00:36:01,481 --> 00:36:03,041
Of course. She likes them.

376
00:36:03,402 --> 00:36:05,656
These aren't too many.
Not enough for a week's change.

377
00:36:06,200 --> 00:36:08,376
Li is really good to you.

378
00:36:08,521 --> 00:36:09,722
It's truly enviable.

379
00:36:10,041 --> 00:36:11,001
Liu isn't bad either.

380
00:36:12,001 --> 00:36:13,752
Thank you.
He has to buy me five pairs too.

381
00:36:13,752 --> 00:36:14,601
Mom, what's wrong?

382
00:36:15,041 --> 00:36:16,001
Got a stitch?

383
00:36:16,521 --> 00:36:17,121
- I'm fine.
- I'll carry you.

384
00:36:17,121 --> 00:36:17,762
I'm happy.

385
00:36:18,362 --> 00:36:19,441
No need.

386
00:36:19,922 --> 00:36:21,322
You take Xiaofei to get a haircut.

387
00:36:21,322 --> 00:36:22,744
His hair is like grass.

388
00:36:22,744 --> 00:36:23,521
Give it to me.

389
00:36:23,521 --> 00:36:24,021
Okay.

390
00:36:24,282 --> 00:36:25,001
I'm leaving now.

391
00:36:25,001 --> 00:36:26,041
Okay, take care then.

392
00:36:28,121 --> 00:36:29,041
She looks so happy.

393
00:36:29,121 --> 00:36:29,621
Let's go.

394
00:36:43,402 --> 00:36:45,081
You scared me. When did you get back?

395
00:36:47,041 --> 00:36:47,682
Where's Xiaofei?

396
00:36:48,081 --> 00:36:49,121
They went for a haircut.

397
00:36:50,282 --> 00:36:52,521
Li bought me four pairs of shoes.

398
00:36:54,001 --> 00:36:57,081
I forgot to tell you.
He has moved in to live with us.

399
00:36:58,121 --> 00:37:00,322
He's now my live-in husband.

400
00:37:03,322 --> 00:37:05,882
When are you and Xiaoran
coming back together?

401
00:37:06,161 --> 00:37:07,762
Our whole family should meet formally.

402
00:37:09,242 --> 00:37:11,362
Help me see which pair looks nice.

403
00:37:12,521 --> 00:37:13,722
There are two flat pairs.

404
00:37:17,842 --> 00:37:19,442
Take a look for me. You have good taste.

405
00:37:19,762 --> 00:37:21,080
These two flat pairs.

406
00:37:21,080 --> 00:37:23,064
Pick one pair for me.
See which one I should keep.

407
00:37:23,282 --> 00:37:24,161
I'll return the other.

408
00:37:24,242 --> 00:37:25,912
No need to spend so much. Help me pick.

409
00:37:52,081 --> 00:37:54,481
This is bizarre. What's going on today?

410
00:37:54,722 --> 00:37:56,001
Everyone's giving me shoes.

411
00:37:57,322 --> 00:37:58,561
What brand are your shoes?

412
00:37:59,081 --> 00:37:59,882
Wen's Shoe Shop.

413
00:38:00,561 --> 00:38:01,521
Wen's Shoe Shop?

414
00:38:03,922 --> 00:38:05,402
(Wen's Shoe Shop)
(You know how to make leather shoes?)

415
00:38:05,682 --> 00:38:07,641
(Wen's Shoe Shop in Erdaohezi.)

416
00:38:08,322 --> 00:38:10,601
(Then I want a pair of high-heels.)

417
00:38:11,561 --> 00:38:12,521
(In white.)

418
00:38:21,402 --> 00:38:23,202
Where did you find this pair of shoes?

419
00:38:30,521 --> 00:38:31,481
These are mine.

420
00:38:33,121 --> 00:38:34,001
These are for me.

421
00:39:04,922 --> 00:39:05,802
Whose shoes are these?

422
00:39:13,561 --> 00:39:14,561
Whose shoes?

423
00:39:14,762 --> 00:39:16,242
These are my shoes.

424
00:39:18,081 --> 00:39:20,081
She stitched these for me,
every stitch by hand.

425
00:39:21,001 --> 00:39:22,842
I told her I saw on a calendar

426
00:39:23,041 --> 00:39:26,521
a girl who looked nice wearing jeans
and white leather shoes.

427
00:39:26,521 --> 00:39:28,402
And she really made them for me.

428
00:39:29,762 --> 00:39:31,882
She also said white leather
was hard to find,

429
00:39:31,882 --> 00:39:35,202
and she had to wait for leftover scraps
to piece together.

430
00:39:36,481 --> 00:39:37,682
She had no money.

431
00:39:38,121 --> 00:39:41,842
How did she get a whole piece
of white leather?

432
00:39:43,081 --> 00:39:43,842
Who was she?

433
00:40:01,481 --> 00:40:02,561
She was my Ms. Zhou.

434
00:40:04,041 --> 00:40:05,682
Every time you yelled at me at home,

435
00:40:07,282 --> 00:40:10,202
making me feel I couldn't stay,
I would go to her.

436
00:40:17,282 --> 00:40:19,001
It was Ms. Zhou who gave me warmth

437
00:40:19,882 --> 00:40:20,802
and hope.

438
00:40:25,882 --> 00:40:28,121
Why didn't you tell me
that Ms. Zhou was Wen Yuxiu?

439
00:40:40,362 --> 00:40:41,922
Tell me where she is.

440
00:40:44,202 --> 00:40:46,722
While our family was happily
celebrating the New Year,

441
00:40:49,601 --> 00:40:50,842
she was hemorrhaging alone

442
00:40:52,601 --> 00:40:54,521
and died in a crude clinic.

443
00:41:13,842 --> 00:41:16,946
(Wen Yuxiu's Tomb)

444
00:41:31,282 --> 00:41:34,521
Why didn't you tell me back then
that Ms. Zhou was Wen Yuxiu?

445
00:41:38,521 --> 00:41:40,762
If you had told me earlier,
she wouldn't have died.

446
00:41:41,682 --> 00:41:43,001
I could have found her sooner.

447
00:41:44,441 --> 00:41:46,041
Why borrow from her?

448
00:41:47,362 --> 00:41:48,682
Why didn't you pay her back?

449
00:41:49,682 --> 00:41:51,682
Do you know how important
that money was to her?

450
00:41:53,161 --> 00:41:54,121
If she'd had that money,

451
00:41:54,121 --> 00:41:57,081
she wouldn't have married that beast
or have died.

452
00:42:03,001 --> 00:42:05,481
Why borrow from her?
Do you love money that much?

453
00:42:07,121 --> 00:42:09,882
If she hadn't married that beast,
she wouldn't have died.

454
00:42:10,922 --> 00:42:13,041
What were you thinking,
leaving her a will?

455
00:42:13,041 --> 00:42:14,722
What were you thinking with this will?

456
00:42:14,842 --> 00:42:16,561
What good is that money to her now?

457
00:42:17,362 --> 00:42:19,081
She's already gone.

458
00:42:40,481 --> 00:42:41,202
Ren Meiyan,

459
00:42:42,202 --> 00:42:44,121
I used to think your little schemes

460
00:42:44,922 --> 00:42:46,242
were because life was hard.

461
00:42:46,242 --> 00:42:48,001
But now I see deep down,

462
00:42:48,001 --> 00:42:50,842
you're just selfish,
and you only care about yourself.

463
00:42:51,441 --> 00:42:53,802
Do you think the whole world owes you?

464
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
